To test these predictions between budburst responses to environmental cues and common functional traits (height, SLA, seed mass, and LNC), we merged available data from global databases of plant traits---BIEN \citep{Maitner2018} and TRY \citep{tryDB}---with global budburst data from the OSPREE database of controlled environment studies \citep{Ettinger2020}. We developed a hierarchical Bayesian joint model that predicts phenological responses to forcing, chilling and photoperiod treatments based on species-level trait values, while allowing additional variation due to species. This approach takes a step towards predicting variation via species traits instead of species identity (when traits explain a significant portion of the variation, species identity will explain only a small amount), which could help forecast species phenological responses based on trait values alone. \\ 

